value.value: The interocular distance that is the shortest between the inner margin of compound eyes.
The male genitalia muscle that connects the valvurae.
The conjunctiva that connects two segments.
The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the intersegmental membrane between the pronotum and the mesopectus and inserts on the mesobasalare.
The sclerite that is located on the intersegmental membrane.
The intersegmentalia that is located in between sterna.
The area that is unsculptured and is delimited by striae or punctures.
The carina that extends between the dorsal margin of the antennal rims.
The sternal sclerite in the venter of the ninth abdominal segment between the second valvifers.
The male genitalia muscle that connects the proximal part of parossiculi.
The sternal muscle that connects the lateral margins of the abdominal tergum 9 and extends internally of the external male genitalia.
The male genitalia muscle that connects the dorsal and ventral part of the gonostipes.
The labial muscle that arises from a palpal sclerite and inserts on the palpal sclerite distal to it.
The wing region that is delimited by the plica jugalis.
The carina that is longitudinal and mesal to the antennal base.

The area that is located apically on the gonostyle when it consist only from one sclerite and set off partly by conjunctiva. The kleisiades is never connected to the proximal part of the gonostyle via muscles.
The gland that empties between the base of the hypopharynx and the labium, or on the hypopharynx.
The anatomical structure that is distal to the proximal margin of the first sclerite of the labial palp.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the labium and maxillae.

The appendage that is encircled by the area that is proximally delimited by the lateral margins of the cardo and the posterior stipital sclerite laterally, and the anatomical line that is tangential to the salivary duct and traverses the salivary orifice anteriorly.
The epipharyngeal muscle that arises from the proximal part of the labrum and inserts on the distal epipharyngeal wall.
The seta that is located on the labrum.
The sclerite that is situated along the distal margin of the clypeus and is connected along its proximal margin with the distal margin of the epipharyngeal wall.
The lobe that extends proximally on the distal margin of the medial stipital wall, is adjacent to the basal lacinial sclerite, overlaps the proximal part of the galea.
The larval tagma that is located posterior to the thorax.
The larval tagma that is located anterior to the thorax.
The tagma that is located in the larva.
The larval tagma that is composed of the prothorax, mesothorax and metathorax and is located between the head and the abdomen.
The S9-cupulal muscle that arises sublaterally from S9 and inserts medioventrally on the cupula.
The apodeme that is located laterally on the proximal margin of abdominal tergum 9.
The area that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina.
The projection that is located on the prolpeuron posterolaterally of the epicoxal lobe and bears the procoxal condyle of the propleuron.
The area that is located laterally on the axilla and is delimited medially by the axillar carina.
The bar that extends from the dorsal axillar area to the mesoscutellum.
The area that is located anterolaterally on the basisternum and forms the median propleural site of articulation with the procoxa.
The carina that extends along the lateral margin of abdominal tergite 3.

The gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises anterolaterally of the site of origin of the distodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle and inserts laterally on the penisvalva.
The gonostyle/volsella complex-volsellal muscle that arises medially of the submedian conjunctiva on the distoventral margin of gonostyle/volsella complex.
The inflection that extends along the anterolateral margin of the mesoscutum and fit with the dorsal pronotal inflection.
The apodeme that arises from the base of the mesofurca.

The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises laterally from the lateral mesofurcal arm, laterally to the site of origin  of the median mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.
The projection that is located on the posterodorsal margin of the axillula.
The metacoxal muscle that originates ventrally of the metapleural ridge and inserts anterolaterally on the dorsal margin of the metacoxa.
The anatomical line that is the shortest between the margins of the  median and lateral ocelli.
The ocellus that is paired.
The area of the pronotum that is lateral and delimited medially by the epomial carina.
The area that is located laterally on the propleuron and is delimited by the longitudinal carina of the propleuron.
The area that is located laterally on the propodeum, is delimited posteromedially by the lateral propodeal carina and is delimited laterally by the plica.
The carina that is oblique and arises submedially from the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex and extends to the posterior propodeal projection.
